thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: Pets are allowed in some managed buildings. [BG] A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building. The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more. Fluffy is Tom's cat. Cats are pets. The Olive Garden is a managed building. The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000. Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500. 2000$ is more than $1500.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Tom is allowed to move in an apartment in The Olive Garden with Fluffy.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Pets(x) ::: x is a pet.
ManagedBuilding(x) ::: x is a managed building.
AllowedIn(x, y) ::: x is allowed in y.
Deposit(x) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in x.
EqualOrMore(x, y) ::: The security deposit in x can be either equal to y or more.
Cat(x) ::: x is a cat.
Owner(x, y) ::: x is the owner of y.
Rent(x, y, z) ::: x will rent an apartment in y if and only if he is allowed to move in with z, and the security deposit is no more than $1500.
MoreThan(x, y) ::: x is more than y.
Premises:
∃x (ManagedBuilding(x) ∧ Pets(x)) ::: Pets are allowed in some managed buildings.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → Deposit(x)) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building.
∀x (Deposit(x) → EqualOrMore(x, oneMonthRent)) ::: The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more.
Cat(fluffy) ∧ Owner(tom, fluffy) ::: Fluffy is Tom's cat.
∀x (Cat(x) → Pets(x)) ::: Cats are pets.
ManagedBuilding(oliveGarden) ::: The Olive Garden is a managed building.
EqualOrMore(oliveGarden, 2000) ::: The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000.
Rent(tom, x, fluffy) ↔ (AllowedIn(fluffy, x) ∧ ¬EqualOrMore(x, 1500)) ::: Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500.
MoreThan(2000, 1500) ::: 2000$ is more than $1500.
Conclusion:
AllowedIn(tom, oliveGarden) ∧ AllowedIn(fluffy, oliveGarden) ::: Tom is allowed to move in an apartment in The Olive Garden with Fluffy.
